			OPINE examines the potential opinion phrases in order to identify the actual opinions.
			First, the system finds thesemantic orientation for the lexical head of each poten tial opinion phrase.
			Every phrase whose head word has a positive or negative semantic orientation is then retained as an opinion phrase.
			In the following, we describe how OPINE finds the semantic orientation of words.
